==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lunistice
<hw>Lu"ni*stice</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>luna</ets> moon + <ets>sistere</ets> to cause to stand. Cf.
<er>Solstice</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Astron.)</fld> <def>The farthest point
of the moon's northing and southing, in its monthly revolution.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lunitidal</ent>⟦br⟧
